1
00:00:14,375 --> 00:00:19,813
<i>Connecting old words</i>
<i>that have been used up</i>

2
00:00:20,648 --> 00:00:28,555
<i>I just want to convey</i>
<i>my simple thoughts</i>

3
00:00:28,623 --> 00:00:33,993
<i>That day's faint wind blows away</i>

4
00:00:34,061 --> 00:00:38,122
<i>at the castle ruins of yesterday</i>

5
00:00:39,367 --> 00:00:44,270
<i>I'll laugh with you</i>
<i>and live for the moment</i>

6
00:00:45,006 --> 00:00:51,912
<i>Still that incident</i>
<i>will continue to trouble you, right?</i>

7
00:00:53,314 --> 00:00:56,806
<i>That's why it must be good bye</i>

8
00:00:56,884 --> 00:01:03,790
<i>Leaving nothing behind,</i>
<i>let us share what is left</i>

9
00:01:03,925 --> 00:01:10,990
<i>In time, we'll realize</i>
<i>that it was everything</i>

10
00:01:11,065 --> 00:01:17,732
<i>And sadness will touch our cheeks,</i>
<i>creating a river of tears</i>

11
00:01:18,139 --> 00:01:27,707
<i>Trembling thoughts swept into a vortex</i>
<i>and melting away</i>

12
00:01:39,037 --> 00:01:40,527
<i>Where's the other one?</i>

13
00:01:41,239 --> 00:01:42,171
Hey...

14
00:01:44,242 --> 00:01:45,903
Who are you looking for?

15
00:01:48,380 --> 00:01:52,373
I'll take care of the rest.
Go wash your eyes in that river.

16
00:01:56,555 --> 00:02:00,685
This is my ability...
specializing in assassination, of course.

17
00:02:00,926 --> 00:02:05,488
You can't beat me by just having
a good nose and nails...

18
00:02:06,231 --> 00:02:08,324
You can't beat my ability!

19
00:02:18,343 --> 00:02:21,574
<i>Akamaru... I'm sorry...</i>

20
00:02:21,947 --> 00:02:25,474
<i>Akamaru...</i>
<i>We've always done things together.</i>

21
00:02:25,817 --> 00:02:27,717
<i>We were together</i>
<i>whenever and wherever.</i>

22
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:32,451
<i>However this one time, I'm sunk.</i>

23
00:02:33,058 --> 00:02:37,791
My cells can swim inside
your body as I wish,

24
00:02:37,862 --> 00:02:40,626
and I can even create parts
that are only you.

25
00:02:40,699 --> 00:02:43,463
In other words,
a little bit of a fusion condition...

26
00:02:43,535 --> 00:02:45,901
a sharing of the flesh is what it'll be.

27
00:02:47,239 --> 00:02:49,104
A sharing...?

28
00:02:49,608 --> 00:02:50,836
That's right!

29
00:02:51,176 --> 00:02:54,304
And a cruel way of killing
that only I can accomplish...

30
00:02:55,113 --> 00:02:59,015
the gradual scraping off
of just your cells!

31
00:02:59,618 --> 00:03:00,744
I see...

32
00:03:08,460 --> 00:03:09,552
If that's the case...!

33
00:03:19,170 --> 00:03:22,936
If I do this...
what's gonna happen?

34
00:03:24,909 --> 00:03:28,037
Suicide?! That's ridiculous!

35
00:03:30,482 --> 00:03:32,074
Die with me...

36
00:03:32,417 --> 00:03:38,253
<i>To Each His Own Battle</i>

37
00:04:03,682 --> 00:04:06,480
What are you thinking?!

38
00:04:15,026 --> 00:04:20,760
It's just as I thought...
We <i>are</i> sharing one body, right?

39
00:04:21,232 --> 00:04:22,164
Damn it!

40
00:04:23,268 --> 00:04:27,398
<i>Entering my opponent's body</i>
<i>to avoid any attacks...</i>

41
00:04:28,006 --> 00:04:30,668
<i>that is my Jutsu's greatest advantage.</i>

42
00:04:31,543 --> 00:04:33,204
<i>There hasn't been</i>
<i>a single one before now</i>

43
00:04:33,278 --> 00:04:34,643
<i>who's done this sort of thing.</i>

44
00:04:36,247 --> 00:04:37,407
Are you in pain?

45
00:04:38,249 --> 00:04:41,582
All right then, let's get comfortable now.

46
00:04:43,288 --> 00:04:45,848
Yikes, you idiot!
Stop it!

47
00:04:45,924 --> 00:04:47,482
It's too late!

48
00:05:04,676 --> 00:05:06,473
There's not enough blood...

49
00:05:27,232 --> 00:05:28,164
Damn!

50
00:05:31,936 --> 00:05:32,868
Damn...

51
00:05:33,738 --> 00:05:35,433
Where'd he go?

52
00:05:49,921 --> 00:05:52,219
So he left his little dog behind
and fled.

53
00:05:53,224 --> 00:05:57,820
It's the right decision,
but he's more cold hearted than me.

54
00:06:09,641 --> 00:06:10,403
What?!

55
00:06:10,809 --> 00:06:11,867
It couldn't be!

56
00:06:32,730 --> 00:06:36,257
<i>What a relief...</i>
<i>He's still breathing.</i>

57
00:06:40,572 --> 00:06:41,766
<i>What a relief!</i>

58
00:06:57,355 --> 00:07:00,984
<i>Akamaru... You really gave it your best.</i>

59
00:07:02,126 --> 00:07:05,323
<i>Because of you, I was able to hold up</i>
<i>the enemy for a while.</i>

60
00:07:05,864 --> 00:07:07,627
<i>We've caused injuries</i>
<i>upon the enemy too.</i>

61
00:07:09,267 --> 00:07:13,226
<i>It's enough... You've done enough.</i>

62
00:07:31,556 --> 00:07:33,490
His name is Akamaru.

63
00:07:33,591 --> 00:07:34,319
Huh?

64
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:37,528
Mom... Sis...

65
00:07:38,796 --> 00:07:42,027
From today, you'll take care of him...
Okay?

66
00:07:43,134 --> 00:07:44,192
I will?

67
00:08:01,052 --> 00:08:04,385
I'm Kiba. Nice to meet you, Akamaru.

68
00:08:13,097 --> 00:08:14,928
You!

69
00:08:28,146 --> 00:08:29,841
<i>We've been together forever.</i>

70
00:08:33,985 --> 00:08:35,612
Nice catch, Akamaru!

71
00:08:38,222 --> 00:08:40,884
All right, you did well!

72
00:08:42,093 --> 00:08:43,117
Here we go!

73
00:08:51,936 --> 00:08:53,426
Be more serious about it!

74
00:08:56,941 --> 00:08:58,932
Stop being such a baby!

75
00:08:59,410 --> 00:09:00,342
Mom...

76
00:09:08,620 --> 00:09:10,053
Listen, Kiba...

77
00:09:10,421 --> 00:09:11,752
It's not just you.

78
00:09:12,023 --> 00:09:13,320
Akamaru and you,

79
00:09:13,391 --> 00:09:15,484
the two of you need
to become strong together.

80
00:09:16,694 --> 00:09:19,720
With Akamaru... Together?

81
00:09:23,201 --> 00:09:24,532
Akamaru...

82
00:09:34,846 --> 00:09:36,211
That's right.

83
00:09:40,718 --> 00:09:43,152
Way to go Akamaru! You did it!

84
00:09:43,287 --> 00:09:45,585
Mid-air Dynamic Marking!

85
00:09:46,824 --> 00:09:50,191
Next is mid-air triple somersault!
Take your aim!

86
00:09:57,702 --> 00:09:58,896
Yahoo!

87
00:10:03,574 --> 00:10:05,201
Yahoo!

88
00:10:20,324 --> 00:10:22,622
<i>We'll be together forever</i>
<i>from now on too...</i>

89
00:10:23,695 --> 00:10:26,823
<i>I'll protect you from now on!</i>

90
00:10:34,439 --> 00:10:35,701
That jerk!

91
00:10:36,607 --> 00:10:38,939
Setting up a trap on me!

92
00:10:52,490 --> 00:10:54,082
I'll kill you!

93
00:10:57,662 --> 00:11:01,098
Hey! Sakon! Where are you?! Sakon!

94
00:11:10,475 --> 00:11:11,533
Sakon!

95
00:11:13,544 --> 00:11:14,704
Sakon!

96
00:11:18,282 --> 00:11:20,910
Blah blah blah.
You're such a nuisance, Big Brother.

97
00:11:21,152 --> 00:11:23,848
Your yelling stings my eyes...

98
00:11:25,590 --> 00:11:26,488
Big Brother!

99
00:11:26,958 --> 00:11:29,051
I'll kill him... is what I'd like to do,

100
00:11:29,127 --> 00:11:30,856
but it's almost time for my sleep.

101
00:11:31,596 --> 00:11:34,929
Capture those bastards alive in my place.

102
00:11:35,767 --> 00:11:37,564
When I wake up,
I'll kill them.

103
00:11:38,269 --> 00:11:41,238
All right, Sakon?
Capture them alive...

104
00:11:41,773 --> 00:11:43,502
Yeah, I got it...

105
00:11:44,142 --> 00:11:45,006
But...

106
00:11:45,910 --> 00:11:47,969
The killing part,
we'll do it together.

107
00:12:19,544 --> 00:12:21,273
<i>If I carelessly attack,</i>

108
00:12:21,345 --> 00:12:23,575
<i>he dodges</i>
<i>and I end up attacking myself!</i>

109
00:12:54,779 --> 00:12:55,711
Behold!

110
00:12:55,780 --> 00:12:57,304
Willow Dance!

111
00:13:23,174 --> 00:13:24,505
You!

112
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:43,327
Bones?

113
00:13:53,437 --> 00:13:56,702
This is my... Kekkei Genkai.

114
00:14:25,003 --> 00:14:27,164
<i>What's with this guy...?</i>

115
00:14:27,939 --> 00:14:30,840
<i>Is he attacking with bones sticking out</i>
<i>from all over his body?</i>

116
00:15:07,445 --> 00:15:10,107
<i>He's grabbed his own bone!</i>

117
00:15:22,227 --> 00:15:23,626
It'll be soon...

118
00:15:27,665 --> 00:15:30,634
<i>He's turning the bone...</i>
<i>into a sword!</i>

119
00:15:39,511 --> 00:15:43,277
It's futile. It's not just ordinary bone.

120
00:15:44,416 --> 00:15:48,750
The highest density bone is hard as steel.

121
00:15:48,987 --> 00:15:53,356
So what?! I'll break that bone!

122
00:15:53,858 --> 00:15:56,486
I possess Five Dances.

123
00:15:59,330 --> 00:16:03,858
You'd better not think
you know my strength after just this much.

124
00:16:04,002 --> 00:16:04,866
What?!

125
00:16:08,473 --> 00:16:10,634
I'll specially show you...

126
00:16:11,609 --> 00:16:13,804
the Camellia Dance next.

127
00:16:16,147 --> 00:16:16,977
Come!

128
00:16:18,116 --> 00:16:19,583
I'll crush you!

129
00:16:31,463 --> 00:16:32,452
<i>I did it!</i>

130
00:16:33,798 --> 00:16:34,958
<i>It's a Substitution?!</i>

131
00:16:40,905 --> 00:16:41,872
<i>There!</i>

132
00:16:42,874 --> 00:16:43,772
Damn!

133
00:16:54,085 --> 00:16:57,521
<i>They're getting closer and closer.</i>

134
00:16:59,757 --> 00:17:00,985
<i>Damn!</i>

135
00:17:10,568 --> 00:17:12,900
<i>This isn't good, traces of blood!</i>

136
00:17:14,038 --> 00:17:17,872
<i>Damn, I did save Akamaru</i>
<i>for the time being,</i>

137
00:17:17,942 --> 00:17:19,967
<i>but maybe I went too far.</i>

138
00:17:40,598 --> 00:17:43,260
<i>This smell...</i>
<i>What does it mean?</i>

139
00:17:45,403 --> 00:17:48,998
<i>Why... Why is it that even those guys</i>
<i>are headed to a place like this?!</i>

140
00:17:49,807 --> 00:17:51,672
<i>I don't understand anymore.</i>

141
00:17:52,243 --> 00:17:55,110
<i>In any case,</i>
<i>we need to leave this place quickly.</i>

142
00:17:59,317 --> 00:18:00,409
<i>I can't...</i>

143
00:18:01,252 --> 00:18:03,516
<i>I'm starting to feel light headed</i>
<i>from the pain and loss of blood...</i>

144
00:18:04,589 --> 00:18:06,989
<i>My body won't move at all either...</i>

145
00:18:11,996 --> 00:18:13,361
<i>Akamaru...</i>

146
00:18:47,398 --> 00:18:49,332
<i>He left just his coat...</i>

147
00:18:51,502 --> 00:18:52,332
<i>Huh?</i>

148
00:18:57,942 --> 00:19:00,342
<i>So he fled by floating down the river...</i>

149
00:19:00,979 --> 00:19:02,412
Damn!

150
00:19:08,052 --> 00:19:09,212
Damn!

151
00:19:17,161 --> 00:19:18,128
Damn...

152
00:19:19,297 --> 00:19:20,321
This is it!

153
00:19:21,466 --> 00:19:25,197
So, I've cornered you, you stinking rat!

154
00:19:28,773 --> 00:19:30,297
Pretty impressive...

155
00:19:30,875 --> 00:19:34,902
You timed it well to scatter
the three to attack.

156
00:19:35,980 --> 00:19:37,743
You must have practiced quite a bit, huh?

157
00:19:39,050 --> 00:19:41,177
Since it's a pretty complicated song...

158
00:19:42,620 --> 00:19:43,917
Well now...

159
00:19:44,922 --> 00:19:46,389
Not only did you
immediately understand

160
00:19:46,457 --> 00:19:48,925
that I'm manipulating these guys
with my flute,

161
00:19:49,427 --> 00:19:53,625
you understood how difficult this song is.
You're a pretty impressive punk.

162
00:19:54,899 --> 00:19:58,494
But you can't completely
understand this song.

163
00:19:59,303 --> 00:20:04,741
You're so right...
since art is so foreign to me.

164
00:20:05,743 --> 00:20:09,144
<i>But since she uses that flute</i>
<i>to manipulate,</i>

165
00:20:09,213 --> 00:20:13,479
<i>it means that song must contain</i>
<i>individually specific sound patterns</i>

166
00:20:13,551 --> 00:20:16,952
<i>to control each and every movement</i>
<i>of those guys.</i>

167
00:20:18,022 --> 00:20:21,458
<i>I'm pretty confident</i>
<i>when it comes to just analyzing,</i>

168
00:20:21,726 --> 00:20:23,717
<i>but this time it's not looking good.</i>

169
00:20:27,398 --> 00:20:28,956
<i>The reason is that</i>

170
00:20:29,033 --> 00:20:32,093
<i>I don't understand</i>
<i>musical notes whatsoever.</i>

171
00:20:32,970 --> 00:20:36,133
There's no one that's heard
this song and lived.

172
00:20:36,507 --> 00:20:40,238
Finale, Ninth Passage,
Demon Revolution!

173
00:20:53,624 --> 00:20:55,091
<i>The melody's changed!</i>

174
00:21:11,376 --> 00:21:13,776
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

175
00:21:13,845 --> 00:21:16,871
<i>And you smiled</i>

176
00:21:17,115 --> 00:21:19,413
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

177
00:21:19,484 --> 00:21:22,214
<i>In my own words</i>

178
00:21:22,287 --> 00:21:27,850
<i>Would you think it was</i>
<i>a bother if I approached you?</i>

179
00:21:28,126 --> 00:21:33,393
<i>Despite my doubts,</i>
<i>I worked up my courage</i>

180
00:21:33,665 --> 00:21:39,069
<i>My clumsy attempts with words</i>

181
00:21:39,271 --> 00:21:44,800
<i>You listened without turning away</i>

182
00:21:45,711 --> 00:21:50,978
<i>No wonder I get carried away by you</i>

183
00:21:51,383 --> 00:21:58,050
<i>But you don't feel anything for me, do you?</i>

184
00:21:58,557 --> 00:22:01,253
<i>I feel so sad</i>

185
00:22:01,326 --> 00:22:02,224
<i>But...</i>

186
00:22:02,294 --> 00:22:04,694
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

187
00:22:04,763 --> 00:22:07,732
<i>And you smiled</i>

188
00:22:07,866 --> 00:22:10,460
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

189
00:22:10,535 --> 00:22:13,527
<i>In my own words</i>

190
00:22:13,705 --> 00:22:16,037
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

191
00:22:16,108 --> 00:22:19,236
<i>And you smiled</i>

192
00:22:19,311 --> 00:22:21,779
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

193
00:22:21,847 --> 00:22:24,748
<i>In my own words</i>

194
00:22:24,883 --> 00:22:29,377
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

195
00:22:37,929 --> 00:22:41,524
Attacks and defense without gaps
using three Summoned bodies.

196
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:44,797
I hate to admit, but she may
be a pretty good Shogi player.

197
00:22:45,170 --> 00:22:47,900
Plus I don't have much Ninja tools left...

198
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:51,539
Man, it feels like I'm playing
without rooks or bishops.

199
00:22:52,110 --> 00:22:53,338
Now then... shall I go?

200
00:22:53,512 --> 00:22:57,278
Cry or laugh,
I can only give it my all here!

201
00:22:57,983 --> 00:23:02,147
Next time,
"Fakeout: Shikamaru's Comeback!"
